  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "8:11-21 Obstinate unbelief will have something to say, though ever so unreasonable. Christ refused to answer their demand. If they will not be convinced, they shall not. Alas! what cause we have to lament for those around us, who destroy themselves and others by their perverse and obstinate unbelief, and enmity to the gospel! When we forget the works of God, and distrust him, we should chide ourselves severely, as Christ here reproves his disciples. How is it that we so often mistake his meaning, disregard his warnings, and distrust his providence?",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Sighed deeply in his spirit - His heart was deeply affected at their wickedness and hypocrisy. The word \"spirit\" here is taken as the seat of the emotions, passions, affections. He drew groans deeply from his breast.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "No sign be given - That is, no such sign as they asked, to wit, a sign \"from heaven.\" He said a sign should be given, the same as was furnished by Jonas, Matthew 16:4. But this was not what they \"asked,\" nor would it be given \"because\" they asked it.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "No sign be given - That is, no such sign as they asked, to wit, a sign \"from heaven.\" He said a sign should be given, the same as was furnished by Jonas, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Matthew 16:4",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". But this was not what they \"asked,\" nor would it be given \"because\" they asked it.",
            "children": []
