    "name": "Geneva Study Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cverse2",
        "text": "And he {c} sighed deeply in his spirit, and saith, Why doth this generation seek after a sign? verily I say unto you, {d} There shall no sign be given unto this generation.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "And he ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "cverse3",
            "text": "{c}",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " sighed deeply in his spirit, and saith, Why doth this generation seek after a sign? verily I say unto you, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "cverse3",
            "text": "{d}",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " There shall no sign be given unto this generation.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(c) These sighs came from the centre of his heart for the Lord was very much moved with the great unbelief of these men.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(d) Literally, If a sign be given. It is an abbreviated kind of speech very common among the Hebrews; it is the same as when we say, Let me be taken for a liar, or something similar. And when they speak out the whole, they say, The Lord do such and such by me.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
